      <h1 class="h4 mb-3">5. Replace only selected descendants with <code>het-select</code></h1>
      <div class="tutorial-content mb-4">
        <p>By default, HET replaces the entire target pane. Use <code>het-select</code> when the response contains a full pane but only some descendants inside that pane should be replaced.</p>
        <p>The response still needs to contain the matching target pane. HET then replaces only the listed ids inside that pane.</p>
        <p>The value is a whitespace-separated id list. On submit buttons, <code>het-select=&quot;&quot;</code> explicitly clears a form-level <code>het-select</code>.</p>
        <p>Relevant reference:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="reference/requests#partial-updates-with-het-select">Partial updates with <code>het-select</code></a></li>
          <li><a href="reference/errors#het-select"><code>het-select</code> errors</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <form method="post" action="/preview" target="tutorial-preview" data-tutorial-form>
        <input type="hidden" name="html" data-editor-output="html">
        <input type="hidden" name="js" data-editor-output="js">
        <input type="hidden" name="css" data-editor-output="css">

        <div class="mb-3">
          <label class="form-label fw-semibold" for="html-source">HTML</label>
